.068806,0.059411,0.049856,0.038805]},{"section":5,"text":"At home, he's also talkative and disorganized.","dimension":9,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.077207,0.14057,0.12607,0.11563,0.092072,0.082361,0.078486,0.069386,0.062794,0.057452,0.052847,0.04512],"unified_progress":[0.0941,0.12417,0.10601,0.10192,0.089594,0.091079,0.078837,0.083624,0.071195,0.062611,0.053712,0.04315]},{"section":6,"text":"He was born at term, no complications, up-to-date on vaccines, and met all developmental milestones on time.","dimension":0,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.054764,0.11896,0.12495,0.1074,0.099148,0.090576,0.086471,0.078968,0.072479,0.067584,0.056779,0.041911],"unified_progress":[0.10111,0.13647,0.10951,0.10293,0.087267,0.089831,0.07528,0.083197,0.068067,0.058948,0.049613,0.037767]},{"section":7,"text":"His IQ test came back at 95, which is average, not super high or low.","dimension":7,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.0465,0.085519,0.10875,0.10954,0.11471,0.10746,0.099708,0.085378,0.075535,0.065968,0.0569,0.044033],"unified_progress":[0.066905,0.10288,0.10351,0.10378,0.10444,0.097498,0.091423,0.084645,0.076908,0.067818,0.057489,0.042696]},{"section":8,"text":"The physical exam is normal, and he can read fluently from a children's book without mistakes.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041828,0.080979,0.097573,0.10582,0.10684,0.10587,0.10283,0.093348,0.082438,0.073146,0.062505,0.046827],"unified_progress":[0.055559,0.089439,0.095739,0.10121,0.10322,0.098647,0.095532,0.089977,0.087359,0.075183,0.061977,0.046157]},{"section":9,"text":"So, the key points here are the sudden drop in academic performance, increased talkativeness, disorganization, and inattention in class.","dimension":9,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.06869,0.12137,0.10393,0.10204,0.083293,0.078988,0.079693,0.073383,0.070541,0.07078,0.072454,0.074833],"unified_progress":[0.079387,0.10606,0.092653,0.089699,0.08507,0.085024,0.082221,0.085204,0.078718,0.075814,0.072106,0.068044]},{"section":10,"text":"He's not hyperactive, as there's no mention of hyperactivity, but more about being lost and not completing tasks.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.047197,0.081337,0.091497,0.089454,0.089901,0.090568,0.091092,0.092525,0.091528,0.090133,0.083962,0.060807],"unified_progress":[0.051282,0.075453,0.079947,0.084689,0.092488,0.093519,0.094299,0.099179,0.095554,0.096048,0.081164,0.056378]},{"section":11,"text":"His reading skills are fine, so it's not a reading disorder.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.045435,0.066833,0.081717,0.087565,0.090019,0.09305,0.094574,0.096109,0.095353,0.094832,0.088058,0.066456],"unified_progress":[0.044742,0.065378,0.075879,0.08304,0.091574,0.093428,0.096959,0.10053,0.099573,0.10065,0.086063,0.062178]},{"section":12,"text":"I'm thinking this might be something related to attention.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037183,0.072086,0.083163,0.09395,0.091223,0.091014,0.096303,0.092445,0.089777,0.097088,0.083334,0.072435],"unified_progress":[0.030775,0.065455,0.081616,0.095091,0.096013,0.095997,0.10183,0.098803,0.095428,0.095089,0.081009,0.062895]},{"section":13,"text":"Since he's not hyperactive but is off-task, maybe it's attention deficit disorder, specifically attention-deficit/hyperactivity disorder (ADHD).","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046133,0.066241,0.077992,0.085555,0.090348,0.093176,0.096577,0.095706,0.094153,0.093139,0.083763,0.077216],"unified_progress":[0.043522,0.06522,0.078057,0.087022,0.092337,0.096813,0.097834,0.098084,0.095066,0.092193,0.082731,0.07112]},{"section":14,"text":"But since there's no hyperactivity mentioned, it's more likely ADHD, predominantly inattentive type.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041867,0.05723,0.070724,0.078123,0.083488,0.088462,0.092981,0.097216,0.099675,0.10187,0.099059,0.089306],"unified_progress":[0.038163,0.056933,0.069686,0.079162,0.087053,0.091656,0.094883,0.099694,0.09989,0.10402,0.095488,0.083377]},{"section":15,"text":"The talkativeness could be a way of trying to cope or because he's not engaged, so he's talking to himself or others to stay awake or focused.","dimension":0,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.056503,0.070636,0.077796,0.082149,0.08626,0.090714,0.094191,0.095595,0.095633,0.092489,0.084603,0.07343],"unified_progress":[0.057775,0.070053,0.076853,0.082199,0.088092,0.094108,0.094505,0.097237,0.095081,0.093039,0.083471,0.067585]},{"section":16,"text":"The IQ being average doesn't rule out ADHD because many kids with ADHD have average or even above-average IQs.","dimension":7,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04499,0.06457,0.081064,0.086466,0.093199,0.095549,0.096926,0.095319,0.094177,0.090702,0.084061,0.072976],"unified_progress":[0.05005,0.072744,0.081869,0.087262,0.092158,0.094434,0.094859,0.095379,0.092014,0.09046,0.081254,0.067518]},{"section":17,"text":"The fact that he met developmental milestones on time doesn't necessarily conflict with ADHD, as it's about attention and behavior, not cognitive delay.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.045782,0.05977,0.075852,0.082082,0.08825,0.092853,0.096384,0.098655,0.099301,0.097992,0.091001,0.072077],"unified_progress":[0.049716,0.067861,0.076634,0.082492,0.090137,0.093247,0.095423,0.098977,0.096551,0.098456,0.085262,0.065244]},{"section":18,"text":"So, putting it all together, the most likely diagnosis is ADHD, specifically the inattentive type, as he's not hyperactive but is struggling with attention and focus in school.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026957,0.041849,0.04867,0.054104,0.058038,0.063801,0.070977,0.080882,0.09348,0.11135,0.1436,0.20629],"unified_progress":[0.02374,0.037606,0.046324,0.055937,0.060689,0.071456,0.076219,