ctions, disorganized, etc.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.057838,0.096819,0.090423,0.088599,0.090862,0.093593,0.09232,0.091765,0.083614,0.080464,0.070758,0.062943],"unified_progress":[0.070828,0.088914,0.090926,0.091077,0.091915,0.094397,0.09074,0.092148,0.084472,0.080589,0.068572,0.055421]},{"section":19,"text":"Hyperactivity includes fidgeting, leaving seat, running around, excessive talking, blurting out answers, etc.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.057692,0.10012,0.09446,0.090547,0.091775,0.094825,0.092002,0.091638,0.081905,0.078011,0.068002,0.059021],"unified_progress":[0.062344,0.088134,0.09411,0.09467,0.094541,0.098053,0.092714,0.092527,0.084725,0.07969,0.066372,0.05212]},{"section":20,"text":"In this case, the boy is talkative, doesn't finish work (inattention), makes careless mistakes, gets distracted (looking around), which are all inattention and hyperactivity symptoms.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.058695,0.098474,0.092265,0.087033,0.087577,0.090627,0.088858,0.089837,0.083686,0.080476,0.07528,0.067192],"unified_progress":[0.07055,0.086191,0.086214,0.087086,0.089187,0.093656,0.089538,0.09157,0.086569,0.082667,0.074986,0.061785]},{"section":21,"text":"The fact that his academic performance dropped when school became more demanding might be a trigger.","dimension":6,"group":2,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04765,0.084817,0.087829,0.089852,0.09294,0.096094,0.094761,0.093388,0.08782,0.084154,0.076429,0.064266],"unified_progress":[0.096758,0.083425,0.082158,0.084306,0.087069,0.089107,0.087372,0.090012,0.083992,0.082519,0.073122,0.060159]},{"section":22,"text":"Since his IQ is normal and he can read well, it's more about attention and behavior rather than a learning disorder.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040686,0.077841,0.085874,0.089946,0.092999,0.095707,0.095395,0.094066,0.089696,0.087174,0.079683,0.070932],"unified_progress":[0.067785,0.082967,0.084748,0.087712,0.089475,0.090798,0.089378,0.090986,0.086222,0.085098,0.07778,0.067051]},{"section":23,"text":"Other possibilities?","dimension":12,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030754,0.068418,0.088693,0.095842,0.097932,0.095078,0.094922,0.092795,0.091196,0.091291,0.080487,0.072592],"unified_progress":[0.037812,0.073455,0.084951,0.10008,0.097706,0.094562,0.097369,0.0924,0.089151,0.09395,0.077594,0.060971]},{"section":24,"text":"Maybe anxiety?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023481,0.058924,0.077888,0.08802,0.097141,0.099321,0.10285,0.10409,0.10084,0.097368,0.086779,0.063302],"unified_progress":[0.053239,0.071505,0.086662,0.095447,0.098555,0.096737,0.10097,0.097771,0.091729,0.087813,0.070533,0.049041]},{"section":25,"text":"But anxiety might present with different symptoms like worry, physical complaints, not necessarily the hyperactivity.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023098,0.055399,0.069409,0.079083,0.088948,0.095486,0.10458,0.10805,0.10624,0.10323,0.096686,0.069794],"unified_progress":[0.035211,0.061626,0.075551,0.082826,0.094462,0.09715,0.10042,0.10616,0.10331,0.10461,0.085061,0.053616]},{"section":26,"text":"Oppositional defiant disorder?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027645,0.062218,0.074705,0.08386,0.092459,0.097817,0.10243,0.10378,0.099782,0.09794,0.087786,0.069576],"unified_progress":[0.042989,0.06645,0.080001,0.089032,0.094472,0.098792,0.10048,0.10119,0.096793,0.095009,0.078736,0.056061]},{"section":27,"text":"But the main issue here is inattention and hyperactivity, not defiant behavior.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028979,0.061905,0.072482,0.080035,0.087454,0.093299,0.10004,0.10278,0.10147,0.099642,0.094399,0.07751],"unified_progress":[0.04204,0.062687,0.073298,0.080651,0.089498,0.093698,0.096673,0.10183,0.10037,0.10398,0.088864,0.06642]},{"section":28,"text":"ADHD is the most likely.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02622,0.057981,0.074237,0.081091,0.083393,0.083287,0.087215,0.088607,0.091196,0.097666,0.098037,0.13107],"unified_progress":[0.028869,0.047758,0.057339,0.068581,0.07188,0.078896,0.085641,0.089283,0.094123,0.10315,0.12237,0.15211]},{"section":29,"text":"The key is that the symptoms started at a certain age and are affecting his school performance.","dimension":6,"group":2,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03715,0.070128,0.076132,0.080702,0.085461,0.089422,0.092659,0.094402,0.094566,0.095144,0.093141,0.091095],"unified_progress":[0.060052,0.060517,0.065166,0.071161,0.077292,0.083776,0.086937,0.09369,0.096928,0.10148,0.10322,0.099776]},{"section":30,"text":"The fact that his early years were fine but then in second grade, when schoolwork becomes more structured, the issues appeared.","dimension":6,"group":2,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036184,0.070845,0.077457,0.083434,0.090563,0.097408,0.098877,0.099403,0.09613,0.092428,0.086652,0.070617],"unified_progress":[0.11062,0.085508,0.078733,0.07761,0.080839,0.084093,0.083947,0.090723,0.084269,0.083969,0.076071,0.063618]},{"section":31,"text":"That's classic for ADHD, where the demands of the classroom environment become too much.","dimension":6,"group":2,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035404,0.067253,0.077726,0.087152,0.094222,0.096766,0.10075,0.098773,0.094452,0.091548,0.084154,0.071802],"unified_progress":[0.11196,0.076197,0.077445,0.080528,0.084142,0.085834,0.085698,0.091387,0.082711,0.08499,0.074432,0.06468]},{"section":32,"text":"So putting it all together, the diagnosis should be ADHD, probably combined type since both inattention and hyperactivity are present.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031967,0.057729,0.065451,0.071447,0.077099,0.081536,0.086772,0.08982,0.094387,0.096433,0.10306,0.1443],"unified_progress":[0.038235,0.048761,0.057975,0.067528,0.068595,0.076791,0.079307,0.084903,0.09593,0.10021,0.12574,0.15602]},{"section":33,"text":"The normal IQ and reading skills rule out intellectual disability or learning disorders.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028448,0.060769,0.073303,0.080346,0.085937,0.090484,0.09529,0.096899,0.098309,0.098261,0.096718,0.095235],"unified_progress":[0.04005,0.060871,0.069585,0.076066,0.082025,0.086765,0.089138,0.094466,0.097593,0.101,0.10236,0.10008]},{"section":34,"text":"The physical exam being normal also fits because ADHD is a neurobehavioral disorder without physical signs.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031796,0.065247,0.076057,0.082912,0.088126,0.092489,0.096078,0.096986,0.096808,0.095767,0.091222,0.086511],"unified_progress":[0.041232,0.064566,0.073237,0.080046,0.085821,0.089792,0.092524,0.095627,0.096544,0.098398,0.094829,0.087385]},{"section":35,"text":"I think that's it.","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.30995,0.051128,0.051846,0.060745,0.062097,0.064182,0.062483,0.070742,0.071657,0.068656,0.07183,0.054684],"unified_progress":[0.20393,0.078567,0.06471,0.064354,0.073918,0.074481,0.091504,0.083835,0.081169,0.066666,0.060653,0.05621]},{"section":36,"text":"The most likely diagnosis is Attention-Deficit/Hyperactivity Disorder (ADHD).","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.051027,0.10057,0.045518,0.074498,0.076648,0.083551,0.081375,0.084567,0.087081,0.087736,0.09155,0.13588],"unified_progress":[0.051878,0.061848,0.044168,0.06529,0.069662,0.078152,0.083147,0.081775,0.086197,0.094674,0.11591,0.1673]}]}}